<br>
They glanced over to the scene and smiled lightly, smiling as best they could being bringers of insanity and death. But they wanted to know more about this . . Goddess.<br>
<br>
A few of the half-gods looked around sensing something there, but their mortal sides kept the Furies images hidden to their eyes. Like it has been said. . .only another immortal can view an immortal without permission.<br>
<br>
Alecto grinned and stood over Ayla.<br>
<br>
&quot;We have been watching you for sometime Goddess.&quot;<br>
<br>
Megaera grinned and stood in front of her.<br>
<br>
&quot;You have brought great interest to Olympus child.&quot;<br>
<br>
Ayla was not a child. . .however to them, even Hera was a young one. Their niece to be exact.<br>
<br>
Tisiphone looked over Ayla smiling lightly.<br>
<br>
Megaera spoke, &quot;Tisiphone can't talk you know. Her meer voice can only be withstood by another Furie. The sound of it brings pure insanity to those who are close enough to hear.&quot;<br>
She grinned wickedly.<br>
<br>
Alecto stepped in front of the other two.<br>
<br>
&quot;Mind not my sister Megaera. She lacks patience with strangers, and intelect with her own.&quot;<br>
<br>
Megaera hissed at Alecto and stood down.<br>
<br>
Alecto turned back to Ayla.<br>
<br>
&quot;We saw you young Goddess. We saw you leave the pressence of Dionysus.&quot;<br>
<br>
Alecto stepped closer to her studying the young one. <br>
<br>
&quot;I see a bit of fear in your eyes. Many mortals fear us yes, but No God or Goddess is feared by uis unless they have something to hide.&quot;<br>
<br>
Tisiphone looked into Ayla's eyes then rushed over to Megaera whispering in her ear.<br>
<br>
Megaera almost fell to the ground with laughter then looked up at Alecto and Ayla.<br>
<br>
&quot;Our new friend has a secret.&quot;<br>
<br>
Alecto sighed and asked calmly as best she could.<br>
<br>
&quot;And what is this secret sister?&quot; To Megaera.<br>
<br>
Megaera grinned. &quot;Tisiphone knows. . .Tisiphone knows all young Goddess.&quot;<br>
<br>
Tisiphone smiled softly to herself as she watched her elder sister roll over the ground in insane laughter.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sister.&quot; Alecto said to Tisiphone. &quot;What is this secret?&quot;<br>
<br>
Tisiphone smiled at Ayla and then vanished in a whirl of black flames.<br>
<br>
Alecto smirked and turned back to Ayla.<br>
<br>
&quot;Trust in the sister Furie to keep your secret young one. For no God would hear Tisiphone speak it on their own will.&quot;<br>
<br>
Megaera stood and calmed down a bit looking to Ayla.<br>
<br>
&quot;I seek your name young goddess. What call you?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> XVDIONYSUS</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FFFF33>(3/11/01 7:32:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Dionysus</span><hr size=1> ::as soon as he sees The girl leave he runs threw olympus shouting and screaming he runs threw the grand hallway where all the gods live. He wakes them all up and tell us that there is a girl here and he felt she was a half god by her presense and that the furies are there now with her. The gods were alarmedby the news and do was dionysus. ::he thought to himself:: i cant wait to meet this mortal she reminds my of someone but i cant place who. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> GuardianAyla</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FFFF33>(3/15/01 4:08:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> In the Woods</span><hr size=1> Ayla took a deep breathe. She apologized immeadiately for taking so long to answer. Her shock at the appearance of the three goddesses, and the fact that one of them now knew her secret scared her. But she answered quietly, &quot;My name is Ayla, Guardian of women and divine children.&quot; She flashed them a welcoming smile, but inside she was screaming. Tisiphone knew the secret. Then an even greater fear entered her heart. If these goddesses could find her so easily, so could the other gods. She smiled and stood. &quot;Forgive me, but you didn't happen to notice any...other gods watching me on Olympus did you?&quot; she asked eagerly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/utheerinyes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Erinyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(3/15/01 11:58:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reflection of Youth...</span><hr size=1> Alecto smiled. &quot;Only Dionysus, he's nothing to worry about.&quot;<br>
